<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-606-862  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 606 862.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Sept 4 1989 v8 n18 p64(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Pub. Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software AG adds 2 new elements to data system. (Software AGSuperNatural 2.3) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taft, Darryl K.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software AG of North America Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Super Natural 2.3 (Program development software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware PackagesUpgradingSpreadsheetsStatistical SoftwareOffice Automation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Software AG Adds 2 New Elements to Data SystemandM;Software AG of North America Inc. has expanded its Super Natural end-userinformation system with two new components that have seen use in thegovernment.andM;With Super Natural Release 2.3, the Reston, Va., company has added theNatural Spreadsheet, a mainframe spreadsheet, and Natural Statistical Link, amenu-driven interface, to the SAS System, a statistical software package fromSAS Institute Inc., Cary, N.C.andM;Software AG's end-user reporting and information management system nowincludes data analysis and statistical functions.andP;  The new version alsoincludes an application interface with other Software AG products.andM;Joseph Reid, chief of information systems at the Centers for Disease Controlin Atlanta, said he uses several Software AG products, including Adabas, thecompany's flagship mainframe database management system.andM;Though Reid said he views some aspects of Super Natural as &quot;not veryuser-friendly,&quot; he likes Natural 2, the company's fourth-generation query andreport writing language.andP;  Although Reid said workers at the Center do not usethe Natural Spreadsheet, they do use the Natural Statistical Link.andM;&quot;We use Natural 2 extensively.andP;  We use it for all administrative andscientific projects,&quot; Reid said.andP;  The scientific projects include systemsthat give public health officials around the country access to mortality,disease and accident data, he said.andM;The Natural Statistical Link is an interactive interface to the SAS Systemfor statistical and graphic analysis.andM;The Natural Spreadsheet, a mainframe spreadsheet product, supportsthree-dimensional processing and unlimited spreadsheet size, companyofficials said.andM;The product is compatible with PC products, such as Lotus Development Corp.'sLotus 1-2-3, as well as mainframe database management systems.andM;Super Natural 2.3 runs on IBM-type mainframes under different operatingsystems.andP;  Prices range from $7,500 to $57,600.andM;Contact Howard Winer, Software AG, tel.andP;  703-860-5050.andO;</TEXT></DOC>